500 g Ground Chicken
1 unit(s) Crushed Tomatoes with Garlic and Onion
113 g Mirepoix
170 g Spaghetti
¼ cup Parmesan Cheese, shredded
1 unit(s) Chicken Broth Concentrate
2 tbsp Balsamic Glaze
1 unit(s) Ciabatta Roll
56 mL Cream
28 g Baby Spinach
3 unit(s) Garlic, cloves
3 tbsp Unsalted Butter*
¼ tsp Pepper*
1 tbsp Oil*
¼ tsp Salt*

Heat a large non-stick pan over medium-high heat. When hot, add 1 tbsp (2 tbsp) oil, then chicken. Cook, breaking up turkey into smaller pieces, until no pink remains, 4-5 min.** Season with salt and pepper.
While chicken cooks, peel, then mince or grate garlic.

A dd spaghetti to the boiling water. Cook uncovered, stirring occasionally, until tender, 10-12 min. Reserve 1/4 cup (1/2 cup) pasta water, then drain and return spaghetti to the same pot, off heat.

While spaghetti cooks, add mirepoix, half the garlic and 1 tbsp (2 tbsp) butter to the pan with chicken. Cook, stirring often, until mirepoix softens slightly, 2-3 min.

Add crushed tomatoes, cream, broth concentrate and balsamic glaze. Season with salt and pepper. Bring to a boil over high.
Once boiling, reduce heat to medium. Cook, stirring occasionally, until sauce thickens slightly, 4-6 min. Remove the pan from heat. Add 1 tbsp (2 tbsp) butter and spinach. Stir until spinach wilts, 1-2 min.

While sauce cooks, combine remaining garlic and 1 tbsp (2 tbsp) butter in a small bowl. Season with salt, to taste.
Halve ciabatta. Arrange on an unlined baking sheet, cut-side up. Spread garlic butter over ciabatta. Sprinkle cheese onto top. Bake in the middle of the oven until cheese melts, 1-2 min. (TIP: Keep an eye on them so they don't burn!)

Add sauce to the pot with spaghetti, then toss to combine. (TIP: For a lighter sauce consistency, add reserved pasta water, 1-2 tbsp at a time, if desired.)
Divide spaghetti between plates. Serve cheesy garlic toast alongside.

If you've opted for double chicken, cook it in the same way the recipe instructs you to cook the regular portion of chicken. Work in batches, if necessary.